{% comment %} FAQ Section {% endcomment %}
<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div class="faq-container">

    <header class="faq-header">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="faq-title">Custom Patches FAQ</h2>
      <p class="faq-subtitle">Find answers to common questions about our custom patches and services</p>
    </header>

    <div class="faq-grid">

      <!-- Column 1 -->
      <div class="faq-col">
        {%- assign faqs_col1 = "Why are custom patches so expensive?|We keep our prices competitive â€” starting as low as $1.34 per patch. Costs vary based on size, stitch count, quantity, and patch type. Ordering in bulk significantly reduces the per-unit price. We also offer no setup fees and free digital proofs.~~What is the difference between embroidered patches and sublimated patches?|Embroidered patches use thread stitched onto a fabric base, giving a textured 3D look. Sublimated (printed) patches use dye infused directly into the fabric for photo-realistic, full-color designs with a flat finish. Embroidered is classic and durable; sublimated is best for complex artwork or gradients.~~Can you turn a photo into a patch?|Yes! Send us any photo, logo, or artwork and our design team will convert it into a patch-ready file. We provide a free digital proof before production begins so you can approve the design.~~What is the best fabric for custom patches?|Twill fabric is the most common and durable base for embroidered patches. For PVC patches, a flexible rubber compound is used. Woven patches use a tighter weave for fine detail. The best choice depends on your patch type and intended use.~~Are iron-on patches worth it?|Absolutely. Iron-on patches are quick to apply, cost-effective, and hold well on cotton, denim, and polyester. For extra durability, we recommend sewing around the edges after heat application." | split: "~~" -%}

        {%- for faq in faqs_col1 -%}
          {%- assign parts = faq | split: "|" -%}
          {%- assign faq_id = 'home-faq-1-' | append: forloop.index -%}
          <div class="faq-item">
            <input class="faq-toggle" type="checkbox" id="{{ faq_id }}">
            <label class="faq-btn" for="{{ faq_id }}">
              <span class="faq-accent"></span>
              <h3 class="faq-question">{{ parts[0] }}</h3>
              <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>{{ parts[1] }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>

      <!-- Column 2 -->
      <div class="faq-col">
        {%- assign faqs_col2 = "How many patches is too many?|There's no limit! We handle orders from 10 pieces to tens of thousands. Whether you need a small batch for a team or a large run for a corporate event, we scale to your needs with consistent quality.~~What payment methods do you accept?|We accept all major credit cards (Visa, Mastercard, Amex), PayPal, and other secure payment methods at checkout. All transactions are encrypted and secure.~~How can I contact customer service?|You can reach us via email, live chat on our website, or by phone at 1-888-499-7708 (Monâ€“Fri, 9AMâ€“5PM EST). Our team typically responds within a few hours.~~Do you ship internationally?|Yes, we ship worldwide. Free shipping is available on qualifying US orders. International shipping rates and delivery times vary by destination. Contact us for a shipping quote.~~How do I track my order?|Once your order ships, you'll receive a tracking number via email. You can use this to monitor your delivery in real time through our shipping carrier's website." | split: "~~" -%}

        {%- for faq in faqs_col2 -%}
          {%- assign parts = faq | split: "|" -%}
          {%- assign faq_id = 'home-faq-2-' | append: forloop.index -%}
          <div class="faq-item">
            <input class="faq-toggle" type="checkbox" id="{{ faq_id }}">
            <label class="faq-btn" for="{{ faq_id }}">
              <span class="faq-accent"></span>
              <h3 class="faq-question">{{ parts[0] }}</h3>
              <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </label>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>{{ parts[1] }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "FAQ",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [{ "name": "FAQ" }]
}
{% endschema %}

